docker container run command:-
Below are the points related to docker container run command:
1. Looks for the image locally in image cache, doesnt find anything, then looks in remote repository (default to https://hub.docker.com).
2. Docker load the latest version  of the image (default tag is: tatest, ex: nginx:latest)
3. Creates a new container based on that image and prepares to start.
4. Gives it a virual ip on a private network inside docker image
5. Openup port (ex: nginx port 80) on a host and forward to port (such as port 80 ) in docker container
6. Start container by using command(cmd) in the image docker file
7. Containers are not mini virtual machines, and they are just processes. They are limited to what resources that tey can access. They exit when process stops
examples:-
1.docker container run --publish 80:80 --name alc-web -d nginx:latest
2.docker container run [options] image [command] [args...]
3.docker container ls 
4.docker container run -p 80:80 -d --name alc_web_nginx nginx:1:11
5.docker container run -p 8080:80 -d --name alc_web_apache httpd
6.docker container exec -it alc_web_apache /bin/sh
7.docker container run -it --name my_alc_web nginx /bin/bash
  Note: The hostname of the container is same as the container name
